as thanks for letting me go.

254
00:10:38,583 --> 00:10:39,375
[MASTER gasps]

255
00:10:39,458 --> 00:10:40,666
But, apparently,

256
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:42,166
I can't go.

257
00:10:42,250 --> 00:10:44,416
So, I guess I'll just have
to lug it back to Moonflower,

258
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:46,625
and stress-eat it all
by my lonesome.

259
00:10:46,708 --> 00:10:47,833
Wait! Hold on, Aoi,

260
00:10:47,916 --> 00:10:49,625
why don't we just
calm down here?

261
00:10:49,708 --> 00:10:51,916
I can't speak for you,
but I am calm.

262
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,291
[MASTER sighs]

263
00:10:54,875 --> 00:10:55,833
[AOI]
Uh--

264
00:10:56,875 --> 00:10:58,958
[drawer opens, rummaging]

265
00:10:59,958 --> 00:11:01,708
[MASTER]
Ahh, there it is.

266
00:11:01,791 --> 00:11:03,958
Mm, what are you doing
over there?

267
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:09,000
[AOI gasps]

268
00:11:09,083 --> 00:11:10,666
Hey...

269
00:11:10,750 --> 00:11:12,458
What...?

270
00:11:12,541 --> 00:11:13,625
[MASTER]
There we go.

271
00:11:13,708 --> 00:11:16,083
[AOI gasps]

272
00:11:16,166 --> 00:11:17,500
Wow.

273
00:11:17,583 --> 00:11:20,041
[humming]

274
00:11:22,083 --> 00:11:24,083
[AOI gasps]

275
00:11:24,166 --> 00:11:27,041
It's a stone that
contains my ogre fire.

276
00:11:27,125 --> 00:11:29,166
Keep it close to you
at all times.

277
00:11:29,250 --> 00:11:30,500
So, it's an amulet?

278
00:11:30,583 --> 00:11:31,583
Indeed.

279
00:11:31,666 --> 00:11:33,416
I ask that you remain
close to Ginji

280
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:35,000
because it truly is dangerous.

281
00:11:35,083 --> 00:11:36,541
Don't wander off without him.

282
00:11:36,625 --> 00:11:37,791
[AOI]
Then I can go?!

283
00:11:37,875 --> 00:11:39,958
If you can keep those
two promises, then yes,

284
00:11:40,041 --> 00:11:42,083
you may go to
the eastern land tomorrow.

285
00:11:42,166 --> 00:11:45,250
Heh. Thank you, Master,
I really appreciate it.

286
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:46,750
So...

287
00:11:46,833 --> 00:11:49,208
I believe you had
a bento for me?

288
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:50,291
[AOI]
Yeah, yeah.

289
00:11:50,375 --> 00:11:51,875
[MASTER]
To be frank,

290
00:11:51,958 --> 00:11:54,916
it makes me happy that I'll get
to enjoy some food you've made.

291
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,666
You must be pretty
hungry to say that.

292
00:11:57,750 --> 00:11:59,666
[MASTER]
Well, no, not quite,

293
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:01,125
but I'll happily eat it.

294
00:12:01,208 --> 00:12:03,375
I'm just thankful
you made it for me.

295
00:12:05,083 --> 00:12:06,125
[AOI gasps]

296
00:12:09,125 --> 00:12:10,333
[gasps]

297
00:12:10,416 --> 00:12:12,750
Huh. Perhaps a thunder beast
has just flown by.

298
00:12:12,833 --> 00:12:14,791
This isn't the first time
our lights have gone out

299
00:12:14,875 --> 00:12:17,375
due to one of their
thunderstorms-- Uh?

300
00:12:19,375 --> 00:12:20,500
Aoi?

301
00:12:20,583 --> 00:12:23,250
I'm sorry for clinging
onto you like this.

302
00:12:23,333 --> 00:12:26,000
I don't do so well with
thunder and lightning.

303
00:12:28,958 --> 00:12:31,958
[AOI crying]

304
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,000
Aoi.

305
00:12:34,083 --> 00:12:35,291
[AOI gasps]

306
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:40,041
[MASTER]
Don't worry.

307
00:12:40,125 --> 00:12:42,625
You don't have to be
scared any longer.

308
00:12:43,875 --> 00:12:45,208
[AYAKASHI]
Don't worry.

309
00:12:45,291 --> 00:12:48,333
You don't have to be
scared any longer.

310
00:12:48,416 --> 00:12:50,958
[AOI] Have I heard
that somewhere before?

311
00:12:53,041 --> 00:12:55,125
[AOI]
Thank you. Really.

312
00:12:55,208 --> 00:12:57,083
That's a beautiful flame.

313
00:12:57,166 --> 00:12:58,166
I'm surprised to learn that

314
00:12:58,250 --> 00:13:00,000
there's something
you're afraid of.

315
00:13:00,083 --> 00:13:00,916
Heh.

316
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:02,875
It's kinda pathetic, isn't it?

317
00:13:02,958 --> 00:13:03,833
Mm?

318
00:13:03,916 --> 00:13:05,250
[AOI gasps]

319
00:13:05,333 --> 00:13:07,875
Don't look so concerned
for my clothes.

320
00:13:07,958 --> 00:13:09,791
If it puts you at ease,

321
00:13:09,875 --> 00:13:11,833
I don't care how
wrinkled they get.

322
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:13,666
Hey...

323
00:13:13,750 --> 00:13:15,750
There's something
I'd like to ask you about.

324
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:17,875
Back when I was a little girl,

325
00:13:17,958 --> 00:13:18,791
I...

326
00:13:22,125 --> 00:13:24,791
Actually, on second
thought, never mind.

327
00:13:25,666 --> 00:13:28,083
[footsteps]

328
00:13:30,958 --> 00:13:33,125
Thank you for walking me
all the way here.

329
00:13:33,208 --> 00:13:35,500
I hope you enjoy
your trip tomorrow.

330
00:13:35,583 --> 00:13:36,791
Get some rest.

331
00:13:37,625 --> 00:13:39,375
[AOI]
Good night, Master.

332
00:13:45,250 --> 00:13:47,208
[AOI'S MOTHER] Don't go outside,
no matter what.

333
00:13:47,291 --> 00:13:49,333
You got that?
Keep the door shut tight,

334
00:13:49,416 --> 00:13:51,041
even if someone comes by.

335
00:13:55,916 --> 00:13:58,250
Come back, Mommy.

336
00:13:58,333 --> 00:13:59,791
[thunder claps]

337
00:14:04,750 --> 00:14:06,000
[groaning]

338
00:14:07,416 --> 00:14:09,500
It was that
same dream again.

339
00:14:11,666 --> 00:14:12,916
[amulet hums]

340
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:15,083
This feels so warm.

341
00:14:17,291 --> 00:14:18,500
Huh?

342
00:14:19,291 --> 00:14:21,083
[AOI]
What's all this?

343
00:14:24,333 --> 00:14:27,416
[MASTER] This bento you made
was quite delicious.

344
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:29,125
The thunder and lightning
may be gone,

345
00:14:29,208 --> 00:14:32,166
but there are plenty of other
frightening things out there.

346
00:14:32,250 --> 00:14:36,041
So, please return to Tenjin-ya
as soon as possible today.

347
00:14:37,333 --> 00:14:38,458
[AOI]
Simmering pork belly

348
00:14:38,541 --> 00:14:40,875
in carbonated water
makes it taste great.

349
00:14:40,958 --> 00:14:42,791
I'm glad he agrees.

350
00:14:42,875 --> 00:14:43,791
[giggles]

351
00:14:43,875 --> 00:14:45,750
[AOI]
But, he sure is a worrier.

352
00:14:45,833 --> 00:14:49,000
Once again, he sounds
just like my grandpa.

353
00:14:49,083 --> 00:14:50,375
[AOI sighs]

354
00:14:50,458 --> 00:14:53,000
He calls me his bride,
but treats me like a child.

355
00:14:53,083 --> 00:14:54,708
It's so weird. Like,

356
00:14:54,791 --> 00:14:56,750
he might as well be my guardian.

357
00:14:57,583 --> 00:14:59,500
[BYAKUYA] You sound like
you're her guardian.

358
00:14:59,583 --> 00:15:01,791
I'm finding it hard
to follow your logic.

359
00:15:01,875 --> 00:15:03,125
If you're that worried,

360
00:15:03,208 --> 00:15:05,250
why did you ever grant
her permission to travel?

361
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:07,750
Aoi isn't a bird
in a cage, you know.

362
00:15:07,833 --> 00:15:09,125
Also,

363
00:15:09,208 --> 00:15:11,666
she strongly wished to pick
the ingredients herself.

364
00:15:11,750 --> 00:15:12,833
[BYAKUYA grunts]

365
00:15:12,916 --> 00:15:15,583
I'm sure she's taking this
very seriously.

366
00:15:15,666 --> 00:15:17,833
That's the kind of woman she is.

367
00:15:19,791 --> 00:15:21,083
[MASTER]
She's probably arriving

368
00:15:21,166 --> 00:15:23,375
in the eastern land
right about now.

369
00:15:26,583 --> 00:15:28,541
[AOI]
Wow! Heh!

370
00:15:28,625 --> 00:15:30,541
It's beautiful!

371
00:15:30,625 --> 00:15:33,416
It's just like the oceans
back in the apparent realm.

372
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:34,791
Uh--

373
00:15:34,875 --> 00:15:36,833
[whales singing]

374
00:15:40,375 --> 00:15:43,291
Well, except for the flying
rainbow whales, that is.

375
00:15:43,375 --> 00:15:45,458
If you look ahead,
you can see how close we are

376
00:15:45,541 --> 00:15:47,291
--to the eastern land.
--Huh?

377
00:15:59,416 --> 00:16:01,458
Interesting.
This place is so different.

378
00:16:01,541 --> 00:16:02,666
The buildings are Western.

379
00:16:02,750 --> 00:16:05,125
Not like Ginten.
Or Youto, either.

380
00:16:05,208 --> 00:16:06,791
I'm kind of surprised.

381
00:16:06,875 --> 00:16:08,291
I thought you might be.

382
00:16:08,375 --> 00:16:11,166
This place is also known as,
"the Land of the Sea Gate."

383
00:16:11,250 --> 00:16:12,750
Sea Gate, huh?

384
00:16:12,833 --> 00:16:15,875
[GINJI] It's a harbor town with
a history of flourishing trade.

385
00:16:15,958 --> 00:16:18,208
So the architecture
has lots of influences.

386
00:16:18,291 --> 00:16:19,583
[AOI]
Fascinating.

387
00:16:19,666 --> 00:16:22,000
I notice there are a lot
of fish shops here.

388
00:16:22,083 --> 00:16:23,166
[GINJI]
Right.

389
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:24,791
Actually, we get our
seafood at Tenjin-ya

390
00:16:24,875 --> 00:16:26,750
from the market
in this town as well.

391
00:16:26,833 --> 00:16:28,375
[AOI]
Oh, I see.

392
00:16:29,125 --> 00:16:31,291
Ah! And there it is.

393
00:16:31,375 --> 00:16:32,458
[AOI]
Mm--

394
00:16:32,541 --> 00:16:33,708
[GINJI]
That's the building in which

395
00:16:33,791 --> 00:16:35,875
the foreign delicacy market
is being held.

396
00:16:35,958 --> 00:16:37,041
[AOI]
Wow!

397
00:16:37,125 --> 00:16:38,500
It's pretty big.

398
00:16:39,625 --> 00:16:41,416
[AOI]
This is great!

399
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,291
Look at all this sweet stuff!

400
00:16:43,375 --> 00:16:45,583
Oh, and they have a bunch
of chocolate, too!

401
00:16:45,666 --> 00:16:47,916
Chocolate isn't
all that common yet,

402
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,250
but it's quite popular
among the wealthy.

403
00:16:50,333 --> 00:16:52,041
Were you thinking
about buying some?

404
00:16:52,125 --> 00:16:53,791
I was, but it's expensive.

405
00:16:53,875 --> 00:16:56,791
It costs so much more than
it does in the apparent realm.

406
00:16:56,875 --> 00:16:58,666
Maybe, but they gave us
a big budget.

407
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:00,291
So, let's see...

408
00:17:00,375 --> 00:17:02,166
These three should be fine.

409
00:17:02,250 --> 00:17:03,291
Yeah, sure!

410
00:17:03,375 --> 00:17:04,583
I'll have to make
chocolate sometime,

411
00:17:04,666 --> 00:17:06,416
so we don't have to spend
so much money.

412
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:07,833
Wait, we can't buy this now!

413
00:17:07,916 --> 00:17:10,458
We haven't gotten anything
we came here for yet!

414
00:17:10,541 --> 00:17:12,083
Well, I can't argue with that.

415
00:17:12,166 --> 00:17:14,750
[AOI] Okay, first let's grab
what we need for beef stew.

416
00:17:14,833 --> 00:17:17,750
I want to get some bouillon
and make the sauce from scratch.

417
00:17:17,833 --> 00:17:19,833
Let's head to
the Western section, then.

418
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:25,416
Oh great, they have
cake flour and bread flour!

419
00:17:25,500 --> 00:17:28,208
Flour is used in tons
of different recipes,

420
00:17:28,291 --> 00:17:30,416
and it looks like
they have dry yeast, too!

421
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:32,041
[GINJI]
What's that used for?

422
00:17:32,125 --> 00:17:34,291
Usually just for baking bread.

423
00:17:34,375 --> 00:17:35,208
Aoi...

424
00:17:35,291 --> 00:17:37,416
Do you know how to make bread?

425
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:39,000
Yeah!

426
00:17:39,083 --> 00:17:41,041
I read a lot about it when I was
in high school and never forgot.

427
00:17:41,125 --> 00:17:42,708
Could I still get
some milk and butter

428
00:17:42,791 --> 00:17:44,500
if you contact
our dairy supplier?

429
00:17:44,583 --> 00:17:46,166
I was planning to bake
some nice rolls

430
00:17:46,250 --> 00:17:47,708
to go along
with the main course.

431
00:17:47,791 --> 00:17:49,125
It'll be great!

432
00:17:49,208 --> 00:17:52,416
Yeah, I bet! Good thing we have
that dairy connection.

433
00:17:53,333 --> 00:17:54,625
[AOI]
Here we go!

434
00:17:54,708 --> 00:17:55,875
Spices!

435
00:17:55,958 --> 00:17:58,500
[GINJI] Oh! They've got
curry mix here, too!

436
00:17:58,583 --> 00:17:59,916
Huh?

437
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:02,000
I have to say, I was quite fond
of the curry and rice

438
00:18:02,083 --> 00:18:04,041
that you made when you
came back to the hidden realm.

439
00:18:04,125 --> 00:18:05,833
I could eat a ton of it.

440
00:18:05,916 --> 00:18:07,166
[giggles]

441
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:09,375
That's just because
the curry roux was so good.

442
00:18:09,458 --> 00:18:10,833
Do you wanna buy
some of those?

443
00:18:10,916 --> 00:18:12,208
Yes, absolutely!

444
00:18:13,125 --> 00:18:15,583
I guess you like curry
a lot, huh Ginji?

445
00:18:15,666 --> 00:18:16,833
[GINJI]
Huh?

446
00:18:16,916 --> 00:18:19,166
Well, it's not so much
that I like it.

447
00:18:19,250 --> 00:18:20,750
I just thought curry
was your favorite,

448
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:22,333
so I figured
we should get some.

449
00:18:22,416 --> 00:18:23,541
That's all!

450
00:18:24,333 --> 00:18:25,625
[AOI]
This isn't the first time

451
00:18:25,708 --> 00:18:27,916
he's said something
like that to me.

452
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:31,791
I'm very hungry.
It's making my stomach hurt.

453
00:18:31,875 --> 00:18:35,708
And all I want now
is my mom's curry and rice.

454
00:18:36,375 --> 00:18:38,125
[AOI]
That couldn't be, right?

455
00:18:38,208 --> 00:18:39,333
[GINJI]
Uh! Aoi!

456
00:18:39,416 --> 00:18:40,875
--Hey, Aoi!
--[AOI] Huh?

457
00:18:40,958 --> 00:18:42,208
Look what I found!

458
00:18:43,458 --> 00:18:44,916
Saké!

459
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:47,416
[AOI] That's the last thing
we needed for the beef stew.

460
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:49,916
I almost wanna
buy some for myself.

461
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:52,416
It's tempting, since it's
from the other realm.

462
00:18:52,500 --> 00:18:54,333
I take it you
like alcohol, then?

463
00:18:54,416 --> 00:18:56,333
I'd be lying if I said no.

464
00:18:56,416 --> 00:18:57,916
What about you, Aoi?

465
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,458
I've never had any.

466
00:18:59,541 --> 00:19:01,541
I only recently became of age.

467
00:19:01,625 --> 00:19:02,791
Oh?

468
00:19:02,875 --> 00:19:04,833
Then why don't we all
have a drinking party?

469
00:19:04,916 --> 00:19:06,750
You, me, and the Master!

470
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:08,166
I'd love for us to get together

471
00:19:08,250 --> 00:19:10,041
and celebrate
your drinking debut!

472
00:19:10,125 --> 00:19:11,166
Uh...

473
00:19:11,250 --> 00:19:12,291
Wait a second.

474
00:19:12,375 --> 00:19:14,375
You wanna drink
and you need an excuse.

475
00:19:14,458 --> 00:19:15,916
[GINJI]
Uh, it's not like that.

476
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:16,958
[AOI]
Hmm...

477
00:19:17,041 --> 00:19:19,041
I swear, that wasn't
my intention.

478
00:19:19,125 --> 00:19:20,625
[giggling]

479
00:19:22,625 --> 00:19:23,458
[AOI sighs]

480
00:19:23,541 --> 00:19:25,041
I'm starving.

481
00:19:25,125 --> 00:19:27,333
Would you like to have some of
the delicious local seafood?

482
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:28,666
Oh, yeah!

483
00:19:35,666 --> 00:19:37,583
The ocean is beautiful.

484
00:19:37,666 --> 00:19:39,291
It always reminds me of the time

485
00:19:39,375 --> 00:19:41,083
when I lived
in the southern land.

486
00:19:41,166 --> 00:19:42,291
If I'm not mistaken,

487
00:19:42,375 --> 00:19:43,791
you worked at an
inn there, right?

488
00:19:43,875 --> 00:19:46,208
Yes, it was a beautiful
inn called Orio-ya,

489
00:19:46,291 --> 00:19:48,333
constructed right
by the seashore.

490
00:19:48,416 --> 00:19:50,875
Oh, wow. I might have
to visit it someday.

491
00:19:50,958 --> 00:19:52,458
Come to think of it,
Hakkabou told me

492
00:19:52,541 --> 00:19:54,541
that he bought his mask
in the southern land, too.

493
00:19:54,625 --> 00:19:56,333
That's a funny coincidence.

494
00:20:01,041 --> 00:20:03,125
--[jingling]
--Uh?

495
00:20:06,041 --> 00:20:08,375
[jingling]

496
00:20:12,250 --> 00:20:13,625
Heh.

497
00:20:13,708 --> 00:20:15,083
[gasps]

498
00:20:18,875 --> 00:20:21,083
[jingling]

499
00:20:21,166 --> 00:20:22,458
Hold on!

500
00:20:22,541 --> 00:20:23,708
[GINJI]
Aoi!

501
00:20:27,208 --> 00:20:29,541
[AOI]
My legs won't stop moving.

502
00:20:29,625 --> 00:20:30,833
Why?

503
00:20:37,166 --> 00:20:38,416
[gasps]

504
00:20:39,833 --> 00:20:40,708
Aoi?

505
00:20:40,791 --> 00:20:42,583
Why don't you take a little nap?

506
00:20:46,208 --> 00:20:47,708
[jingling]

507
00:20:51,916 --> 00:20:54,125
[rain pouring]

508
00:20:54,666 --> 00:20:56,541
[sigh]

509
00:20:56,625 --> 00:20:58,625
Raining?

510
00:20:58,708 --> 00:20:59,916
Hold on.

511
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:01,166
What?

512
00:21:01,250 --> 00:21:03,750
How'd I... get here?

513
00:21:03,833 --> 00:21:06,125
It smells like the ocean.

514
00:21:10,666 --> 00:21:12,958
[AOI]
Am I locked in a storeroom?

515
00:21:13,041 --> 00:21:16,083
Oh, maybe I can
use Matsuba's fan.

516
00:21:16,916 --> 00:21:17,833
[AOI]
It's gone!

